      "content": "I hear how heavy and final that feeling of a \"finished story\" sounds, and it makes sense why you feel exhausted from pretending someone is still inside you when it feels like they've already left. That sense of reading blank pages over and over can be incredibly draining, and it's okay to feel that the effort to find a \"real\" version of yourself is futile right now.\n\nSometimes, when we feel this disconnected, our minds can create a narrative where the \"real\" person died long ago, leaving us as a ghost in our own skin. While it might feel like the story is truly over, it's worth remembering that even if the plot has stalled, the characters (including you) are still on the page, even if the ink is fading.\n\nIf this sense of emptiness and exhaustion feels too heavy to carry alone, please consider reaching out to a mental health professional or a crisis line. They can offer a safe space to talk through these feelings without judgment, and help you find ways to make the blank pages feel less like a void and more like a space for new possibilities. You don't have to face this exhaustion by yourself.",
